A Cape Town poultry farm has been prohibited from using an area where two workers died, while investigations continue. eNCA's Silindelo Masikane has more details. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A Cape Town poultry farm has been prohibited from using an area where two workers died while investigations continue. The workers died and others were injured at County Fair Poultry last week. READ: 7 workers found dead on FS farm Employment and Labour Minister, Thulas Nxesi, and other officials visited on Friday. Nxesi says his department is looking into the matter. County Fair Poultry has declined to comment.